
 Private registry

Registry blue.sky is configured as a local private registry(TLS & basic auth).
TLS: self-signed certificates
Basic authentication: test/test

https://github.com/docker/distribution/blob/v2.2.1/docs/deploying.md

-) Create self-signed certificate
  # mkdir -p certs && openssl req \
    -newkey rsa:4096 -nodes -sha256 -keyout certs/domain.key \
    -x509 -days 365 -out certs/domain.crt

  FQDN: blue.sky
  
-) Create password file:
 # mkdir auth
 # docker run --entrypoint htpasswd registry:2 -Bbn test test > auth/htpasswd

-) Deploy certiifcates, edit (set FQDN) and execute script
  # ./deployBlueskyCertificates.sh.sh

-) Start bluesky/private registry:
  # docker-compose -f bluesky-registry.yml up -d

-) Util
  .) show images
      https://localhost:5000/v2/_catalog
  .) show tags for a given image
      https://localhost:5000/v2/bookstore/tags/list


